  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed dwelling would give rise to a cramped form of development, on an uncharacteristically small plot, giving rise to garden sizes which are materially out of keeping with that prevailing in the locality and resulting in an intrusive and overbearing form of development when seen from the streetscene and the wider rear garden environment, harmful to local character and contrary to Policy D6 of the London Plan (adopted 2021).",
    "The proposed dwellinsg would, by reason of their location and  proximity close to the shared boundaries either side of the site, appear as an unacceptably dominant and visually intrusive feature, harmful to the established local pattern of development  within the surrounding area. It would therefore be harmful to the character and appearance of the surrounding area contrary to Local Plan Policies 7 and 26.",
    "The proposed two storey dwelling would, by reason of its scale, bulk and mass, position close to the boundaries of the site and position of upper floor windows, give rise to an intrusive and unneighbourly form of development, resulting in harm to the privacy and amenity of occupiers of neighbouring property at nos. 8 and 10 Malvern Road contrary to the provisions of Local Plan Policy 7 and 10.",
    "The proposed two storey dwelling would, by reason of the low ceiling heights, result in a low quality design that would be to the detriment of future occupants, contrary to the provisions of Policy D6 of the London Plan (adopted 2021).",
    "The proposed single storey dwelling would, by reason of the flat roof, result in a low quality design that would be out of character in the area, contrary to the provisions of Policy 26 of the Havering Local Plan",
    "The proposed access to the site, by the reason of it size would be significantly narrow for vehicular access to the detriment of both vehicular and pedestrian safety, contrary to the provisions of Policy 23 and 24 of the Havering Local Plan.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: Consideration was given to seeking amendments, but given conflict with adopted planning policy, notification of intended refusal was given to the agent via email on July 2022."
  ],
